Kamfanin dillancin labarai na Associated Press ya zargi sakataren yada labarai na fadar White House Kayleigh McEnany da damun kafafen yada labarai ta hanyar sanya bayanan ta na siyasa maimakon bayani - a fili ya manta cewa 'yan jarida sun zabi tambayoyin.
Wani labarin Asabar ta AP, babbar kamfanin dillancin labaran Amurka, ya ce taron manema labarai na Fadar White House na iya zama "wani al'ada da aka karya", kamar yadda McEnany ya sanya su "sanannen sanarwa, mai cike da talla ga shugaban da ke fuskantar sake za ~ e, wurin da za a kai hari kan kafofin watsa labarai da kuma wani dandalin da ba shi da haske game da bayanai" game da abin da gwamnati ke yi.
Wannan na ƙarshe daga cikin waɗannan maganganun ba shi da wata shakka, kamar yadda kusan ba a bayyana sabon bayani a cikin bayanan ba.
Abin da AP ta kasa ambata shi ne cewa kusan babu wani sabon bayani da ake nema a zahiri a cikin bayanan.
'Yan jarida suna amfani da gidan jaridar White House sau da yawa don jawo hankali ga kansu, wani nau'in fasaha da aka kammala ta hanyar CNN Jim Acosta.
Sun wuce dangantakar adawa da kafofin watsa labarai-gudanar, suna maimaita juna a cikin tambayar tambayoyin gotcha da nufin kawai su kalubalanci Shugaba Donald Trump.
A wasu lokuta, suna sanya kansu labarai, kamar lokacin da mai ba da rahoto na CBS News Weijia Jiang ya amsa "tambayar Sin" ta hanyar yin ba da hankali ba game da wariyar launin fata: "Sir, me yasa kuke faɗin hakan a gare ni musamman?"
