Babban jami'in Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ya tsallake ziyarar Pakistan, yana mai ambaton batun jirgin
ISLAMABAD (AP) - Shugaban Majalisar Dinkin Duniya mai shigowa ya sanar a ranar Lahadi cewa yana jinkirta ziyarar da aka shirya zuwa Pakistan "saboda wasu matsalolin fasaha na jirgin".
An zabi jami'in diflomasiyya na Turkiyya Volkan Bozkir a matsayin shugaban taron Majalisar Dinkin Duniya karo na 75 a watan da ya gabata kuma an shirya isa Islamabad a ranar Lahadi.
Amma a wani sako da ya wallafa a shafinsa na Twitter, ya ce ziyarar zuwa babban birnin Pakistan za ta jira.
Ministan harkokin wajen Pakistan Shah Mahmood Qureshi ya yi ta'aziyya ga Bozkir cewa "Ina fatan in maraba da ku zuwa Pakistan nan ba da jimawa ba don ziyarar mai amfani da amfani".
A ranar da ta gabata, wani Qureshi mai farin ciki, yayin sanar da ziyarar, ya yi fatan zai tattauna da Bozkir kan wasu batutuwa, gami da Kashmir, wanda aka raba tsakanin Pakistan da makwabciyar Indiya kuma duka biyu suna da'awarsa gaba ɗaya.
Pakistan da Indiya sun yi yaƙi biyu daga cikin yaƙe-yaƙe uku a kan yankin da ake jayayya tun lokacin da suka sami 'yanci daga mulkin Birtaniya a 1947.
Bangarorin biyu galibi suna musayar wuta a Kashmir, wanda ke haifar da sojoji da fararen hula a bangarorin biyu.
Pakistan tana son Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ta taka rawar da take takawa wajen warware matsalar Kashmir a karkashin shawarwarin ta ta hanyar barin mutanen da ke zaune a yankin Himalayan su yanke shawara ko suna son hadewa da Indiya, da Pakistan ko kuma ko sun fi son 'yanci.
