Babban Ministan Madhya Pradesh Shivraj Singh Chouhan, wanda a ranar Asabar ya tabbatar da cewa ya kamu da cutar COVID-19, ya yi tweet a safiyar Lahadi don ya ce yana "cikin koshin lafiya" kuma ya ba da yabo ga ma'aikatan gaba a cikin yaki da coronavirus.
Babban Ministan ya kuma maimaita gargadin da ya yi a jiya, lokacin da ya bukaci mutane su bi ka'idoji, kamar nisantar jama'a da amfani da abin rufe fuska.
"Ina lafiya, abokaina. sadaukar da kai na mayakan coronavirus, wadanda ba da son kai suke sadaukar da ransu, abin yabawa ne. Ina gaishe da dukkan mayakan coronavirus na jihar", Mista Chouhan ya wallafa a shafinsa na Twitter daga Asibitin Chirayu na Bhopal, inda aka kwantar da shi a jiya.
"Ku kiyaye tazarar mita biyu, ku wanke hannuwanku akai-akai kuma ku sanya abin rufe fuska - wadannan sune manyan makamai da muke da su don gujewa cutar coronavirus. Ina kira ga dukkan mutane - yi amfani da wadannan makamai don kanku da ƙaunatattunku", in ji shi.
"Dukkanku ku yi hankali, ku kasance cikin koshin lafiya. Wannan shine abin da na yi addu'a ga Allah", in ji Mista Chouhan.
A ranar Asabar Mista Chouhan ya yi tweet cewa ya gwada tabbatacce ga kwayar cutar duk da kokarin da ya yi na kaucewa kamuwa da cutar kuma ya yi gargadin cewa "kawai kadan daga cikin rashin kulawa yana gayyatar coronavirus".
A wani sakon Twitter da ya wallafa a safiyar yau, Mista Chouhan ya ce duk da barazanar kamuwa da cutar, "babu bukatar jin tsoro" kuma ya bukaci wadanda ke nuna alamun cutar da su yi gwajin kansu.
